WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.711 --> 00:00:03.979
[dogs barking]

2
00:00:04.013 --> 00:00:05.149
What do we got?

3
00:00:05.182 --> 00:00:07.153
♪ [spy music plays]

4
00:00:07.153 --> 00:00:09.256
Lost dog's been wandering
the marshland all night.

5
00:00:09.290 --> 00:00:10.927
Every time we approach it.
it goes further

6
00:00:10.961 --> 00:00:11.729
into the wetlands.

7
00:00:11.996 --> 00:00:13.599
Well. this place floods
when the tide comes in.

8
00:00:13.599 --> 00:00:14.534
so we gotta move quick.

9
00:00:14.801 --> 00:00:16.404
I don't think your toy's
big enough to pick up a collie.

10
00:00:16.404 --> 00:00:18.676
My unmanned aerial vehicle
is not for the dog.

11
00:00:18.710 --> 00:00:19.243
It's for the bait.

12
00:00:19.377 --> 00:00:20.580
And my shirtless beach runs.

13
00:00:21.281 --> 00:00:22.985
Bro. that's hickory smoked.

14
00:00:23.018 --> 00:00:24.287
[Frank] Oh. should work
perfectly. then.

15
00:00:24.320 --> 00:00:26.358
That's why you always bring
a backup.

16
00:00:26.726 --> 00:00:28.294
[Frank] Let's roll... or fly.

17
00:00:29.430 --> 00:00:32.369
Just when I think you can't
get any more badass.

18
00:00:33.840 --> 00:00:36.410
♪ [spy music plays]

19
00:00:37.079 --> 00:00:38.281
[dog whines]

20
00:00:41.588 --> 00:00:43.559
[laughs] Hey. you just
sausage slapped him!

21
00:00:43.559 --> 00:00:45.663
Let's keep those words.
in that order.

22
00:00:45.697 --> 00:00:46.364
outta the report.

23
00:00:46.532 --> 00:00:48.335
Ooh. he liked it.
He's following it.

24
00:00:48.368 --> 00:00:50.206
Come on. buddy.
take a little nibble

25
00:00:50.206 --> 00:00:52.076
of Frank's dangling meat.

26
00:00:52.109 --> 00:00:53.211
Good lord.

27
00:00:53.211 --> 00:00:55.081
[Frank] Just a little further.

28
00:00:55.081 --> 00:00:56.417
Come on.

29
00:00:56.618 --> 00:00:57.988
[dog barks]

30
00:00:58.221 --> 00:01:00.292
[gasps] Yes!

31
00:01:01.528 --> 00:01:02.564
[Shred] Yay!

32
00:01:02.597 --> 00:01:03.532
[growling]

33
00:01:05.201 --> 00:01:07.373
Oh...
Yeah. Come on. buddy.

34
00:01:07.406 --> 00:01:08.509
Good boy.

35
00:01:08.943 --> 00:01:10.478
Mission accomplished.

36
00:01:10.513 --> 00:01:12.449
Rough landing. but next time--

37
00:01:13.786 --> 00:01:15.222
[Victoria] Ooh.

38
00:01:15.623 --> 00:01:16.992
Well. he died a hero.

39
00:01:17.192 --> 00:01:19.296
Moment of silence. please.

40
00:01:20.499 --> 00:01:21.569
Oh.

41
00:01:21.602 --> 00:01:23.706
♪ [vocalizing]

42
00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:31.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

43
00:01:54.400 --> 00:01:56.638
Top o' the morning. Frank.

44
00:01:56.905 --> 00:01:58.108
[dog barks]
-Ahh!

45
00:01:58.610 --> 00:02:00.245
You remember my
best friend. Hopper?

46
00:02:00.278 --> 00:02:02.183
Yeah. you mean your best
dog friend [chuckles].

47
00:02:02.416 --> 00:02:03.653
Why is he in the truck?

48
00:02:03.819 --> 00:02:06.124
Well. they're banning dogs
from my building.

49
00:02:06.157 --> 00:02:07.093
I mean. I guess
they already were banned.

50
00:02:07.293 --> 00:02:09.864
And then my idiot neighbor
ratted us out after Hopper

51
00:02:09.864 --> 00:02:11.167
gnawed on her kid's stroller.

52
00:02:11.200 --> 00:02:11.802
Yeah. well. that's something

53
00:02:12.069 --> 00:02:13.138
a human best friend
would never do.

54
00:02:13.304 --> 00:02:16.645
I would move. but Doc Whiskers
just really loves my apartment.

55
00:02:16.645 --> 00:02:18.482
And. you know cats.
they hate change.

56
00:02:18.516 --> 00:02:20.720
That's why I can't ever shave
my beard. so...

57
00:02:20.753 --> 00:02:21.522
Hopper's gotta leave.

58
00:02:21.722 --> 00:02:23.692
Yeah. well. I'm sure
he'll find a great home.

59
00:02:23.725 --> 00:02:26.698
Probably not one with
children or a diverse mailman.

60
00:02:26.698 --> 00:02:28.401
I've also seen him be weird
to women.

61
00:02:28.401 --> 00:02:30.138
I'm making him the precinct dog.

62
00:02:30.138 --> 00:02:31.408
He's just like his old man.
[Hopper barks]

63
00:02:31.441 --> 00:02:33.445
Born leader. full head
of hair. opinionated.

64
00:02:33.513 --> 00:02:35.783
He doesn't seem thrilled
that I'm in the truck. Frank.

65
00:02:35.783 --> 00:02:37.386
Again. like his old man.

66
00:02:37.788 --> 00:02:38.556
[Hopper barks]

67
00:02:38.790 --> 00:02:40.593
[Shred] Yeah. have you cleared
this with Emily?

68
00:02:40.593 --> 00:02:41.896
[Frank] I called her
this morning

69
00:02:41.929 --> 00:02:43.398
but she didn't pick up.

70
00:02:52.884 --> 00:02:54.420
Oh! Uh-uh. hi.

71
00:02:54.454 --> 00:02:56.224
-You're here early.
-Mm-hmm.

72
00:02:56.257 --> 00:02:57.927
And... I'm here late.

73
00:02:57.961 --> 00:02:59.565
I forgot we were supposed
to walk this morning.

74
00:02:59.598 --> 00:03:02.270
I went alone. Like a loser.
It was so embarrassing.

75
00:03:02.303 --> 00:03:03.939
I mean. it was
really nice to do a walk

76
00:03:03.939 --> 00:03:05.375
that wasn't of shame.
but still.

77
00:03:05.409 --> 00:03:06.812
And you bailed
on coffee last week.

78
00:03:06.879 --> 00:03:08.414
-What is happening?
-Um...

79
00:03:08.682 --> 00:03:11.121
Well. I... I do have
a little secret.

80
00:03:11.421 --> 00:03:12.924
So. I guess I'll tell you.

81
00:03:12.957 --> 00:03:13.826
Um...

82
00:03:14.426 --> 00:03:15.797
I started to golf.

83
00:03:16.197 --> 00:03:17.868
-What? Golfing?
-Yeah.

84
00:03:17.901 --> 00:03:19.237
But you hate sports.

85
00:03:19.270 --> 00:03:20.606
Well. I think
what it was is I...

86
00:03:20.640 --> 00:03:22.175
I hadn't found the right sport.

87
00:03:22.175 --> 00:03:23.646
But now I have. and it's golf.

88
00:03:23.679 --> 00:03:26.552
And my coach says
I'm a natural. actually.

89
00:03:26.585 --> 00:03:28.221
And his-his name's Javie.

90
00:03:28.288 --> 00:03:29.624
Is Javie cute?

91
00:03:30.593 --> 00:03:31.628
Yeah.

92
00:03:31.662 --> 00:03:33.800
Oh... really?

93
00:03:33.833 --> 00:03:34.535
Wow. Dish.

94
00:03:34.735 --> 00:03:37.239
Like. did something happen
with Javie?

95
00:03:37.239 --> 00:03:37.941
Yeah. we made.

96
00:03:38.141 --> 00:03:41.347
we made...
we made love to-together.

97
00:03:43.351 --> 00:03:44.587
-No. you didn't.
-Big time.

98
00:03:44.621 --> 00:03:46.490
There is no way
that you made love

99
00:03:46.490 --> 00:03:48.529
with your golf instructor.
Javie. and didn't tell me.

100
00:03:48.562 --> 00:03:49.631
You're hiding something.

101
00:03:49.698 --> 00:03:51.367
Okay. technically. we did not

102
00:03:51.367 --> 00:03:52.738
fully sleep together.
but we did

103
00:03:52.771 --> 00:03:55.141
do a lot of serious
parking lot stuff.

104
00:03:55.175 --> 00:03:57.881
Time for the morning meeting.
Frank's got a crazy dog.

105
00:03:57.914 --> 00:03:58.582
[barking]

106
00:03:58.783 --> 00:04:01.522
So the new snake tongs
will arrive on--

107
00:04:01.522 --> 00:04:02.657
- [barking]
- Oh. uh...

108
00:04:02.657 --> 00:04:05.395
The snake tongs
will be arriving here.

109
00:04:05.395 --> 00:04:06.899
uh. next Wednesd--.
[Hopper barks]

110
00:04:07.567 --> 00:04:09.403
Boss. you want me to put down
that dog?

111
00:04:09.403 --> 00:04:10.973
Hey! Come on. he's a talker.

112
00:04:11.006 --> 00:04:13.278
He was already talking
dangerously close to my groin.

113
00:04:13.278 --> 00:04:14.213
Frank. what's the plan here?

114
00:04:14.447 --> 00:04:16.552
I think we can all agree
that morale at the precinct

115
00:04:16.585 --> 00:04:17.721
is at an all-time low.

116
00:04:17.754 --> 00:04:19.323
-No. it's not.
-What we need...

117
00:04:19.356 --> 00:04:20.559
[Hopper barking]
-is a precinct dog.

118
00:04:20.593 --> 00:04:22.664
Nothing makes people happier
than a mascot.

119
00:04:22.664 --> 00:04:25.302
and Hopper will give us
something to believe in.

120
00:04:25.335 --> 00:04:27.573
And mascots don't usually
foam at the mouth.

121
00:04:27.607 --> 00:04:29.276
I called you this morning
to get the okay

122
00:04:29.309 --> 00:04:29.978
but you didn't answer.

123
00:04:30.144 --> 00:04:31.682
Oh. yeah. because
she was golfing.

124
00:04:31.715 --> 00:04:33.485
Uh. no. No need for
the quote marks.

125
00:04:33.519 --> 00:04:34.654
I was on the links.

126
00:04:34.688 --> 00:04:36.324
[Hopper barking]
-Yeah. Frank. this is...

127
00:04:36.357 --> 00:04:37.560
this is unsustainable.

128
00:04:37.560 --> 00:04:39.631
He just needs to learn
everyone's scent.

129
00:04:39.665 --> 00:04:43.304
Folks. your back door is like
a name tag for a dog. so...

130
00:04:43.337 --> 00:04:44.172
line up and bend over.

131
00:04:44.406 --> 00:04:46.343
Nope. Nobody do that.
Um. okay. we are so close

132
00:04:46.410 --> 00:04:47.413
to finishing this meeting.

133
00:04:47.446 --> 00:04:48.448
[Roman] What. what!

134
00:04:48.448 --> 00:04:51.354
Party people in the house.

135
00:04:51.387 --> 00:04:55.262
Cherise. these are the people
who love to partay.

136
00:04:55.295 --> 00:04:58.502
Guys. this is my intimate
gal pal.

137
00:04:58.536 --> 00:04:59.871
-Cherise.
-Salut.

138
00:04:59.905 --> 00:05:00.640
Welcome. Cherise.

139
00:05:00.873 --> 00:05:03.879
And Roman. so nice
to see you here for...

140
00:05:03.879 --> 00:05:05.382
for. um. for why?

141
00:05:05.415 --> 00:05:07.854
I brought m'lady. French.

142
00:05:07.888 --> 00:05:10.559
here to show off all
my philanthropic efforts.

143
00:05:10.559 --> 00:05:13.733
The kennels that I built.
the murals that I painted.

144
00:05:13.733 --> 00:05:16.304
and the cans of pears
I left behind in the kitchen.

145
00:05:16.337 --> 00:05:17.774
Management only. Shrek.

146
00:05:17.808 --> 00:05:19.645
You only have me
for two more hours.

147
00:05:19.678 --> 00:05:21.548
Oh. Okay. plea-- what did.
what did we say?

148
00:05:21.582 --> 00:05:22.751
-Oop.
[Hopper barks]

149
00:05:22.784 --> 00:05:23.418
Wow!

150
00:05:23.619 --> 00:05:25.556
Who is this little
friendly fellow?

151
00:05:25.590 --> 00:05:28.495
This is Hopper. I know he can
seem a little aggressive.

152
00:05:28.495 --> 00:05:30.666
but he loves surprise kisses.
so get your face in there.

153
00:05:30.699 --> 00:05:31.735
Well. that kinda behavior's

154
00:05:31.735 --> 00:05:33.405
is reflective of poor ownership.

155
00:05:33.438 --> 00:05:34.875
[barking]

156
00:05:34.908 --> 00:05:35.976
Oops.

157
00:05:36.243 --> 00:05:37.914
Okay. meeting adjourned.
Meeting adjourned.

158
00:05:37.948 --> 00:05:40.018
[Hopper barking]

159
00:05:40.252 --> 00:05:42.857
Frank. the dog has got to go.

160
00:05:43.224 --> 00:05:45.361
Hey. guys. Guys.

161
00:05:45.763 --> 00:05:47.499
I got a bite on your flip house.

162
00:05:47.534 --> 00:05:48.836
-What?
-Cool! Who's biting?

163
00:05:48.869 --> 00:05:50.105
Her name's Rebecca.

164
00:05:50.105 --> 00:05:51.776
It's a cash offer.

165
00:05:51.809 --> 00:05:54.346
But she is coming in
25 under asking.

166
00:05:54.380 --> 00:05:55.382
-Under?
-[Shred] Hey.

167
00:05:55.650 --> 00:05:57.653
This thing's been on the market
for ages. that's pretty good.

168
00:05:57.653 --> 00:05:58.622
-Thank you. Bettany.
-It's great.

169
00:05:58.889 --> 00:06:02.362
But I'm wondering if maybe
we should tag me into the deal.

170
00:06:02.362 --> 00:06:03.364
Um...

171
00:06:03.397 --> 00:06:04.535
Um? [laughs]

172
00:06:04.535 --> 00:06:05.402
I'm a closer. baby.

173
00:06:05.637 --> 00:06:08.274
Especially since I read
that FBI negotiator's book.

174
00:06:08.308 --> 00:06:10.613
Turns out there are
a lot of similarities

175
00:06:10.646 --> 00:06:13.752
between selling a house
and freeing a Somalian hostage.

176
00:06:13.786 --> 00:06:15.957
-What?
-Quick sidebar with my man.

177
00:06:15.990 --> 00:06:16.959
Yeah?

178
00:06:17.092 --> 00:06:18.394
-What?
-Hey. so we don't

179
00:06:18.428 --> 00:06:19.430
have any other offers.
-That's true.

180
00:06:19.463 --> 00:06:21.568
So I think what we should
be saying right now

181
00:06:21.568 --> 00:06:22.771
is stuff like.
thank you so much.

182
00:06:22.771 --> 00:06:24.373
Also. what kinda cookies
do you like?

183
00:06:24.406 --> 00:06:25.643
'Cause we're gonna
bake you some.

184
00:06:25.643 --> 00:06:26.745
-Yeah. No. you're right.
-Okay.

185
00:06:26.778 --> 00:06:28.649
-Bettany. we appreciate you.
-Mm-hmm.

186
00:06:28.649 --> 00:06:30.620
And in fact. if there's
anything you need from us.

187
00:06:30.653 --> 00:06:31.254
you just let us know.

188
00:06:31.454 --> 00:06:33.391
-I'm good.
-[Shred] By the way...

189
00:06:33.425 --> 00:06:34.527
What is your favorite cookie?

190
00:06:34.561 --> 00:06:36.464
Aww. you wanna bake me
something sweet?

191
00:06:36.497 --> 00:06:37.166
- Yeah
- We'd love to.

192
00:06:37.399 --> 00:06:39.904
You can bake in
a 10 percent commission.

193
00:06:41.206 --> 00:06:42.142
We were talking about cookies.

194
00:06:42.442 --> 00:06:44.815
[Frank] Don't you worry. buddy.
We'll figure something out.

195
00:06:44.848 --> 00:06:47.386
But for now.
it's not so bad.

196
00:06:47.419 --> 00:06:48.589
There's no scary people

197
00:06:48.622 --> 00:06:51.562
coming around the corner
to startle you.

198
00:06:51.562 --> 00:06:54.066
All the used tennis balls
you can dream of.

199
00:06:56.437 --> 00:06:57.941
[Hopper whines]

200
00:06:57.974 --> 00:07:00.546
Hup. Nope. Done.
We're not doing this. Come on.

201
00:07:00.580 --> 00:07:02.884
We already saw
this wall of giant dogs.

202
00:07:02.917 --> 00:07:04.554
[Hopper barks]
-[Frank] Hopper!

203
00:07:04.588 --> 00:07:06.024
-Hopper. Hopper!

204
00:07:06.057 --> 00:07:08.027
Please stop. Hopper!

205
00:07:10.432 --> 00:07:12.069
You are so powerful.

206
00:07:12.102 --> 00:07:13.839
There's no way that word

207
00:07:13.873 --> 00:07:15.475
means the same thing
in your native language.

208
00:07:15.509 --> 00:07:17.714
-You like that. Cherie baby?
-Oui.

209
00:07:17.714 --> 00:07:19.717
Don't use my dog
in your foreplay.

210
00:07:20.218 --> 00:07:21.922
There is good in this dog.

211
00:07:21.955 --> 00:07:22.857
But he's in
the wrong environment.

212
00:07:23.157 --> 00:07:27.232
I assume you live very much
alone in a sad one-bedroom?

213
00:07:27.232 --> 00:07:29.738
Would a sad one-bedroom have
a burgundy accent wall

214
00:07:29.738 --> 00:07:30.673
in its kitchen/living room?

215
00:07:30.974 --> 00:07:34.981
Burgundy is a trigger color
for most dogs and most people.

216
00:07:34.981 --> 00:07:35.850
You're wearing burgundy.

217
00:07:35.850 --> 00:07:38.655
I can sense when a dog
is not thriving.

218
00:07:38.689 --> 00:07:41.628
It's a working-class breed.
It needs space.

219
00:07:41.662 --> 00:07:43.364
and stimulation.

220
00:07:43.397 --> 00:07:45.570
-And I know just the spot.
-You're gonna say your house?

221
00:07:45.570 --> 00:07:46.604
I'm gonna say my mansion.

222
00:07:46.604 --> 00:07:47.974
Which is a limited time offer

223
00:07:48.007 --> 00:07:49.010
that expires in five...

224
00:07:49.010 --> 00:07:50.946
Pass. Hopper's exactly
where he belongs.

225
00:07:50.979 --> 00:07:53.418
Oh. really? 'Cause he just
left you 10 seconds ago.

226
00:07:53.586 --> 00:07:55.188
[Emily screams]

227
00:07:55.221 --> 00:07:57.492
-Eat the yogurt. not the lady!
-[Emily whines]

228
00:07:57.527 --> 00:07:59.063
[Shred] Live and active cultures
for you.

229
00:07:59.096 --> 00:07:59.931
Just eat the yogurt!

230
00:08:00.198 --> 00:08:02.570
What are you doing?
He's not supposed to eat that.

231
00:08:06.645 --> 00:08:09.417
What happens next time
this is a child?

232
00:08:09.450 --> 00:08:10.418
Or worse.

233
00:08:10.452 --> 00:08:12.423
A famous person.

234
00:08:12.489 --> 00:08:14.827
You need to give me the dog.

235
00:08:14.861 --> 00:08:16.898
Frank. clearly
his snaps are magic.

236
00:08:16.898 --> 00:08:18.668
[Shred] And they do seem
to have a rapport.

237
00:08:18.702 --> 00:08:21.542
You're just jealous because
Hopper asks nothing of me

238
00:08:21.575 --> 00:08:22.476
and I give him everything.

239
00:08:22.710 --> 00:08:24.614
You two have a level of
intimacy that I'm a little bit

240
00:08:24.648 --> 00:08:26.584
jealous of. but I really do
think it's the best thing

241
00:08:26.618 --> 00:08:28.922
for Hopper and for all of us.

242
00:08:30.660 --> 00:08:32.062
Yeah. could somebody
maybe help me down?

243
00:08:32.062 --> 00:08:34.567
'Cause I think my
vertigo is kicking in.

244
00:08:34.601 --> 00:08:35.837
[engine starts]

245
00:08:35.870 --> 00:08:39.076
[Roman] Cherise!
Not where Hopper can see.

246
00:08:43.050 --> 00:08:44.521
Sorry. man.

247
00:08:44.521 --> 00:08:45.322
I know that was tough.

248
00:08:45.523 --> 00:08:47.794
You... wanna grab a beer
and talk about it?

249
00:08:47.827 --> 00:08:50.766
I would. but everyone's
already gone home.

250
00:08:51.802 --> 00:08:53.639
Okay. I know you're joking.
but that...

251
00:08:53.672 --> 00:08:54.841
really hurt.

252
00:08:58.783 --> 00:09:00.753
With the movie White Chicks.
you have to remember

253
00:09:00.787 --> 00:09:02.624
that it's a product of its time.

254
00:09:02.657 --> 00:09:03.793
[TV playing in background]

255
00:09:03.793 --> 00:09:05.663
Where's the remote?

256
00:09:05.897 --> 00:09:07.767
[groans]

257
00:09:10.573 --> 00:09:12.643
♪ [sad music plays]

258
00:09:12.677 --> 00:09:14.581
[Doc Whiskers growls and hisses]

259
00:09:14.614 --> 00:09:15.482
Okay. Doc.

260
00:09:15.716 --> 00:09:18.555
You won the battle.
no need to dance on his grave.

261
00:09:19.056 --> 00:09:20.926
I feel like it's only
a matter of time before

262
00:09:20.959 --> 00:09:22.129
Victoria finds out about us.

263
00:09:22.129 --> 00:09:23.799
I mean. she is
kind of relentless.

264
00:09:23.832 --> 00:09:25.301
I have to ask.
Why golf?

265
00:09:25.301 --> 00:09:26.070
I don't know.
I panicked.

266
00:09:26.303 --> 00:09:28.542
I mean. what else do people do
in the mornings?

267
00:09:28.542 --> 00:09:29.511
Last week before work

268
00:09:29.711 --> 00:09:33.284
you swam. you did yoga.
you went to physical therapy.

269
00:09:33.350 --> 00:09:35.288
Yeah. but those are real
and I needed a lie.

270
00:09:35.288 --> 00:09:37.192
-[Shred] Hmm.
[phone rings]

271
00:09:37.225 --> 00:09:38.796
Oh. Frank's calling.

272
00:09:38.829 --> 00:09:41.234
Probably a butt dial.
but just in case.

273
00:09:41.267 --> 00:09:42.102
-Frank?
-Hey.

274
00:09:42.369 --> 00:09:44.173
What are you doing right now?
You wanna grab a beer?

275
00:09:44.173 --> 00:09:45.141
Uh.

276
00:09:45.175 --> 00:09:46.176
Like. together?

277
00:09:46.176 --> 00:09:46.978
Don't be weird.

278
00:09:47.178 --> 00:09:48.849
Yes. The answer's yes.
I will be right there.

279
00:09:48.882 --> 00:09:51.020
You just drop a pin
and I'm on the way. Okay?

280
00:09:51.053 --> 00:09:51.855
[call ends]

281
00:09:51.855 --> 00:09:53.024
-It's happening.
-Wh--

282
00:09:53.058 --> 00:09:55.061
Frank wants to hang out
outside of work.

283
00:09:55.095 --> 00:09:56.296
[engine revs]

284
00:09:56.330 --> 00:09:57.265
[tires squeal]

285
00:09:57.298 --> 00:09:57.933
Okay.

286
00:09:58.133 --> 00:09:59.671
I'm sorry. I have
to drop you off.

287
00:09:59.704 --> 00:10:01.106
I need to go home
and change tops.

288
00:10:01.106 --> 00:10:02.075
Okay... yeah.

289
00:10:02.342 --> 00:10:04.581
I don't know that I've ever
heard you refer to it as a top.

290
00:10:04.581 --> 00:10:05.583
[quietly squealing]
[phone rings]

291
00:10:05.616 --> 00:10:07.019
Oh. Frank's calling me now.

292
00:10:07.019 --> 00:10:08.989
Okay. No. that's definitely
his butt.

293
00:10:09.023 --> 00:10:10.793
-[Emily] Hey. Frank.
-Hey. What are you doing?

294
00:10:10.826 --> 00:10:12.897
I'm at the golf pro shop.

295
00:10:13.131 --> 00:10:15.970
-[whispers] Why?
-[whispers] I don't know.

296
00:10:16.003 --> 00:10:17.707
Oh. s-sure.

297
00:10:17.740 --> 00:10:19.075
I'll see you there.

298
00:10:19.610 --> 00:10:22.851
I guess I'm coming
to your drinks.

299
00:10:23.318 --> 00:10:25.656
-Oh.
-Oh. hey. I'm-I'm sorry.

300
00:10:25.656 --> 00:10:26.524
It's fine.

301
00:10:26.758 --> 00:10:27.492
It's just. if this seems like
it's heading towards

302
00:10:27.993 --> 00:10:30.899
a bro sleepover. I'm gonna
need you to be cool and bail.

303
00:10:31.266 --> 00:10:32.670
[Bettany] It's morning.

304
00:10:32.704 --> 00:10:36.377
You come downstairs
and the smell of coffee

305
00:10:36.377 --> 00:10:38.047
permeates your new home.

306
00:10:38.114 --> 00:10:39.049
I love coffee.

307
00:10:39.049 --> 00:10:41.120
That is a very generous offer.

308
00:10:41.153 --> 00:10:43.625
Thank you.
I'll call you back.

309
00:10:43.625 --> 00:10:44.393
That's the Saudis.

310
00:10:44.594 --> 00:10:46.798
They're taking a very
aggressive position.

311
00:10:46.831 --> 00:10:49.269
This is Patel.
He's one of the owners.

312
00:10:49.269 --> 00:10:50.873
Hi. Amit Patel.

313
00:10:50.907 --> 00:10:53.344
Rakishly handsome face
from the sign on the yard.

314
00:10:53.378 --> 00:10:54.814
[Bettany and Patel fake laugh]

315
00:10:54.848 --> 00:10:56.819
Will you excuse us for a second?

316
00:10:56.819 --> 00:10:57.654
So good to meet you.

317
00:10:57.887 --> 00:11:00.392
There are no Saudis.
That was a fake offer move.

318
00:11:00.392 --> 00:11:01.762
I told you. I've got this.

319
00:11:01.795 --> 00:11:03.699
I really see myself here.

320
00:11:03.732 --> 00:11:05.636
You know what?
I could see you here too.

321
00:11:05.969 --> 00:11:09.009
Although I could also see
three Saudis sharing shakshuka

322
00:11:09.042 --> 00:11:10.812
over in the breakfast nook.

323
00:11:12.182 --> 00:11:13.284
What's their offer?

324
00:11:13.317 --> 00:11:15.087
Ten thou over asking.

325
00:11:15.087 --> 00:11:17.091
But you could match that and...

326
00:11:17.125 --> 00:11:19.997
we could close this thing
right here. right now.

327
00:11:22.435 --> 00:11:24.173
Okay. let's do it.

328
00:11:24.206 --> 00:11:25.408
R-really?

329
00:11:25.442 --> 00:11:26.143
[laughs] Great.

330
00:11:26.277 --> 00:11:29.149
Glad I was here
to land this plane.

331
00:11:30.820 --> 00:11:32.991
Oh. yay! You made it.

332
00:11:32.991 --> 00:11:34.226
When Frank called. I said.

333
00:11:34.226 --> 00:11:36.096
"Don't forget Shred.
he would love this".

334
00:11:36.130 --> 00:11:36.998
That's not true.

335
00:11:36.998 --> 00:11:39.002
That-that can't be
how it happened.

336
00:11:40.271 --> 00:11:41.975
Emily! Wow.

337
00:11:41.975 --> 00:11:43.646
Boss outside of work.

338
00:11:43.679 --> 00:11:45.182
What a... very fun.

339
00:11:45.248 --> 00:11:47.452
I invited her even though
she banished my dog

340
00:11:47.486 --> 00:11:49.757
from the precinct. sending me
into a crushing depression.

341
00:11:49.791 --> 00:11:50.960
Do you wanna know
what's really cool

342
00:11:50.993 --> 00:11:52.697
about this place
that I picked?

343
00:11:52.697 --> 00:11:54.433
It has a golf simulator.

344
00:11:54.466 --> 00:11:55.836
What? No. it doesn't.

345
00:11:55.869 --> 00:11:57.773
It does. in the other room.
Yeah.

346
00:11:57.807 --> 00:11:59.409
I want to see that swing
of yours. girlfriend.

347
00:11:59.442 --> 00:12:00.311
Uh. totally.

348
00:12:00.546 --> 00:12:02.917
Um. but. you know. tonight's
about our friend. Frank.

349
00:12:02.950 --> 00:12:04.253
so we should
just be there for him.

350
00:12:04.286 --> 00:12:07.392
Don't let my spiral suspend
any mirth.

351
00:12:07.392 --> 00:12:08.261
Go. Fake golf.

352
00:12:08.495 --> 00:12:10.265
Honestly. you ladies
are kinda killin' the vibe.

353
00:12:10.298 --> 00:12:12.035
[Victoria] Okay.
-It's okay. it's what happens

354
00:12:12.068 --> 00:12:13.438
when you get bigger
groups together.

355
00:12:13.471 --> 00:12:14.741
[Victoria] Come on.

356
00:12:14.908 --> 00:12:16.344
Now it's just us.

357
00:12:16.377 --> 00:12:18.248
[grunts] Frank and Beans.

358
00:12:18.716 --> 00:12:20.017
What. you gave yourself Beans?

359
00:12:20.051 --> 00:12:21.955
I actually started with Beans.

360
00:12:23.090 --> 00:12:24.225
2017.

361
00:12:24.259 --> 00:12:25.696
Pre-pandemic.

362
00:12:25.729 --> 00:12:27.132
You're getting a great deal.

363
00:12:27.165 --> 00:12:29.436
House down the street
is asking the same price.

364
00:12:29.470 --> 00:12:30.504
And those dopes.

365
00:12:30.504 --> 00:12:31.742
they don't even have a basement.

366
00:12:31.775 --> 00:12:33.712
I actually don't need
a basement.

367
00:12:33.712 --> 00:12:34.948
It's a flood risk.

368
00:12:34.981 --> 00:12:36.450
Uh. yeah. But. you know.
it's Seattle.

369
00:12:36.483 --> 00:12:37.720
It barely rains here.

370
00:12:37.753 --> 00:12:38.420
Not to mention. you know.

371
00:12:38.588 --> 00:12:39.189
it's really far
from the freeway.

372
00:12:39.590 --> 00:12:41.795
so the commute to work...
[scoffs] hellish.

373
00:12:41.829 --> 00:12:43.264
I work from home.

374
00:12:43.297 --> 00:12:44.332
Oh.

375
00:12:45.301 --> 00:12:48.474
Before I sign.
I think maybe I should

376
00:12:48.508 --> 00:12:49.878
look at that other house.

377
00:12:49.911 --> 00:12:51.113
[Bettany] Other house?

378
00:12:51.146 --> 00:12:53.317
I was gone for
less than a minute.

379
00:12:54.119 --> 00:12:56.256
Okay...

380
00:12:59.129 --> 00:13:00.899
Did you wanna pick a club?

381
00:13:00.932 --> 00:13:01.601
Yeah. yeah.

382
00:13:01.768 --> 00:13:04.774
I like to survey
the terrain first.

383
00:13:04.807 --> 00:13:06.209
You look so at home here.

384
00:13:06.243 --> 00:13:07.780
Yeah. that's...

385
00:13:07.813 --> 00:13:09.082
I know.

386
00:13:11.087 --> 00:13:12.790
That's an interesting way
to grip it.

387
00:13:12.824 --> 00:13:14.193
Yeah. that's what
Javie said too.

388
00:13:14.226 --> 00:13:16.732
But. you know.
he wasn't complaining. so...

389
00:13:16.765 --> 00:13:17.733
Wow.

390
00:13:17.767 --> 00:13:19.469
You are off the rails. Swing.

391
00:13:20.806 --> 00:13:22.543
Jesus. take the club.

392
00:13:27.085 --> 00:13:29.255
-Oh!
-[simulator voice] Good swing.

393
00:13:30.358 --> 00:13:31.393
[notification alert]

394
00:13:33.097 --> 00:13:34.835
[Roman] Yes! Home at last.

395
00:13:34.868 --> 00:13:36.771
Who's a good boy?

396
00:13:36.804 --> 00:13:37.940
Well...

397
00:13:38.508 --> 00:13:40.546
Hopper looks pretty happy.

398
00:13:40.546 --> 00:13:41.848
Celebratory shots?

399
00:13:41.881 --> 00:13:42.984
Yeah! Yeah.

400
00:13:43.017 --> 00:13:46.089
And then after that.
we'll go use the photo booth.

401
00:13:46.089 --> 00:13:48.394
[laughs] I'll photoshop you in.

402
00:13:49.062 --> 00:13:50.966
Meet me in the bathroom.

403
00:13:50.966 --> 00:13:52.837
Victoria is all over me
like a bloodhound.

404
00:13:52.870 --> 00:13:53.839
I can't keep lying.

405
00:13:53.872 --> 00:13:55.642
Well. it just sounds like things
are gettin' away

406
00:13:55.642 --> 00:13:57.880
from you a little bit.
so maybe just call it a night.

407
00:13:57.914 --> 00:13:59.382
Will you just stop trying
to be alone with Frank?

408
00:13:59.382 --> 00:14:01.588
It's getting very weird
and we need an actual plan.

409
00:14:01.588 --> 00:14:03.023
Gotcha!

410
00:14:04.459 --> 00:14:05.830
Are you two hooking up?

411
00:14:05.863 --> 00:14:07.566
Is that why you've been acting
so weird?

412
00:14:07.599 --> 00:14:09.002
[both] No...

413
00:14:09.336 --> 00:14:12.008
That-that... that would.
that would be insane.

414
00:14:12.042 --> 00:14:13.979
-That'd be nuts.
-No. I-I have. I have Javie.

415
00:14:14.012 --> 00:14:15.014
-So...
-Yeah.

416
00:14:15.047 --> 00:14:16.216
Who's... wait. who's Javie?

417
00:14:16.250 --> 00:14:17.887
Babe. that's my golf instructor.

418
00:14:17.920 --> 00:14:19.322
-I told you...
-You just called him babe!

419
00:14:19.356 --> 00:14:20.593
No... damn it.

420
00:14:20.626 --> 00:14:22.262
Okay. yes.
We are hooking up.

421
00:14:22.262 --> 00:14:24.466
But I think it's. like.
more than that.

422
00:14:24.466 --> 00:14:25.301
-Wait. Really?
-Right?

423
00:14:25.535 --> 00:14:27.940
I mean. I do too.
but wasn't sure how you felt.

424
00:14:27.940 --> 00:14:28.609
[faint singing]

425
00:14:28.776 --> 00:14:30.311
Okay. I'm sorry.
It sounds like Frank

426
00:14:30.344 --> 00:14:32.115
is having a karaoke breakdown
out there.

427
00:14:32.148 --> 00:14:35.956
-Is it okay if I just... please.
-Yeah. Yeah. Just... yeah.

428
00:14:37.025 --> 00:14:38.461
Why didn't you tell me?

429
00:14:38.494 --> 00:14:39.597
I didn't tell anyone.

430
00:14:39.630 --> 00:14:40.833
Yeah. but I'm not anyone.

431
00:14:40.866 --> 00:14:42.468
At least I thought I wasn't.

432
00:14:44.105 --> 00:14:46.511
Just one more thing.
'cause I need you to know this.

433
00:14:46.744 --> 00:14:48.213
You ruined golf for me.

434
00:14:48.247 --> 00:14:54.492
♪ Sometimes...
everybody cries. ♪

435
00:14:57.466 --> 00:15:00.438
♪ Everybody hur--

436
00:15:00.471 --> 00:15:02.108
Okay. Okay!

437
00:15:02.275 --> 00:15:03.044
Okay.

438
00:15:03.077 --> 00:15:04.245
♪ Sometimes...

439
00:15:04.279 --> 00:15:05.916
Give it up for Frank. everybody.

440
00:15:05.916 --> 00:15:08.020
Such a soulful performance.
Right? Thank you.

441
00:15:08.054 --> 00:15:10.358
[weak applause]

442
00:15:10.692 --> 00:15:12.095
You were doing so good.

443
00:15:12.129 --> 00:15:13.197
It was the video.

444
00:15:13.932 --> 00:15:15.168
I just miss him so much.

445
00:15:15.201 --> 00:15:17.840
And more than that.
I feel like I failed him.

446
00:15:17.873 --> 00:15:19.309
He's... a perfect dog.

447
00:15:19.342 --> 00:15:22.315
[Man] Next up. we got Frank S.
Tears in heaven.

448
00:15:22.349 --> 00:15:24.352
Okay. I can't stand
to see you like this.

449
00:15:24.352 --> 00:15:26.290
I definitely can't take
another song.

450
00:15:26.290 --> 00:15:26.892
So...

451
00:15:27.092 --> 00:15:28.194
as much as it pains me
to say it.

452
00:15:28.294 --> 00:15:30.398
maybe you should think about
going to get Hopper back.

453
00:15:30.431 --> 00:15:33.137
Do I ask myself why it's
Hopper you love instead of me?

454
00:15:33.170 --> 00:15:34.975
-Yeah.
-You comin'?

455
00:15:34.975 --> 00:15:36.276
Oh. we're going now.

456
00:15:42.556 --> 00:15:44.125
Why are his doors wide open?

457
00:15:44.159 --> 00:15:46.163
[muffled yelling]

458
00:15:46.430 --> 00:15:47.398
[muffled yell]

459
00:15:49.770 --> 00:15:50.772
[muffled yell]

460
00:15:50.806 --> 00:15:52.341
[Frank] Hopper!

461
00:15:54.581 --> 00:15:55.649
Hey.

462
00:15:55.682 --> 00:15:56.618
You okay?

463
00:15:56.985 --> 00:15:59.122
This is a Taken situation.

464
00:15:59.156 --> 00:16:00.191
They took Hopper.

465
00:16:00.424 --> 00:16:02.997
They probably already got him
dancing on some sheikh's yacht.

466
00:16:03.030 --> 00:16:03.765
Cherise?!

467
00:16:03.965 --> 00:16:05.902
Did they take her?
Did they take Cherise?

468
00:16:05.936 --> 00:16:07.239
No. She did it!

469
00:16:07.272 --> 00:16:08.074
She cleaned me out!

470
00:16:08.341 --> 00:16:11.279
Hopper bolted when she was
carrying out my 4K TV.

471
00:16:11.313 --> 00:16:12.115
He's probably looking for me!

472
00:16:12.381 --> 00:16:15.120
I'm such an idiot!
I took a shower this morning.

473
00:16:15.120 --> 00:16:17.391
My musk is weak. so I gotta...

474
00:16:17.425 --> 00:16:19.229
Should I call the police?
I'll call the police.

475
00:16:19.229 --> 00:16:20.699
No. we can't get
the police involved

476
00:16:20.699 --> 00:16:22.134
in me and Cherise's situation.

477
00:16:22.168 --> 00:16:23.403
I can't believe you lost my dog.

478
00:16:23.437 --> 00:16:24.741
-What?
-Here. let me help.

479
00:16:24.741 --> 00:16:25.542
[tape rips]
-Ahhh!

480
00:16:25.743 --> 00:16:27.412
I can't believe I sold
someone else's house.

481
00:16:27.479 --> 00:16:29.951
-I blew it!
-She's just looking. okay?

482
00:16:29.984 --> 00:16:30.886
Just stay positive.

483
00:16:31.186 --> 00:16:33.156
You know. I think of myself
as this hotshot entrepreneur

484
00:16:33.190 --> 00:16:34.793
who can make any deal happen.

485
00:16:34.793 --> 00:16:37.131
Now I'm wondering.
maybe I'm terrible at this.

486
00:16:37.165 --> 00:16:39.770
Okay. look. don't take this
the wrong way.

487
00:16:39.770 --> 00:16:41.106
I'm preparing to be offended.

488
00:16:41.140 --> 00:16:42.442
You're not as smart
as you think you are.

489
00:16:42.442 --> 00:16:44.146
I was ready for it
and it still hurt.

490
00:16:44.179 --> 00:16:45.516
Look. I'm not
calling you a dummy.

491
00:16:45.516 --> 00:16:47.987
I'm just saying you don't
always know what's better.

492
00:16:48.020 --> 00:16:49.356
I had your house sold.

493
00:16:49.389 --> 00:16:51.627
No. You did.
I'm sorry.

494
00:16:53.096 --> 00:16:54.633
Okay. Accepted.

495
00:16:54.867 --> 00:16:56.369
[phone chimes]

496
00:17:01.179 --> 00:17:03.117
She's going with the other
house. isn't she?

497
00:17:03.150 --> 00:17:04.720
-Yup.
-Oh...

498
00:17:04.787 --> 00:17:06.257
Give me that bottle.

499
00:17:06.257 --> 00:17:07.258
Ahh.

500
00:17:08.460 --> 00:17:11.467
It's empty! You stole
my commission and my buzz?

501
00:17:11.500 --> 00:17:13.470
Yeah. I think I'm gonna need
a ride home.

502
00:17:13.470 --> 00:17:15.642
No. You riding the bus. dummy.

503
00:17:15.675 --> 00:17:17.144
Hopper!

504
00:17:17.144 --> 00:17:18.347
Where are you?

505
00:17:18.381 --> 00:17:20.986
Daddy's sorry he abandoned you!

506
00:17:21.020 --> 00:17:22.021
Cherise!

507
00:17:22.055 --> 00:17:24.125
I just wanna talk.

508
00:17:24.192 --> 00:17:25.027
I forgive you.

509
00:17:25.294 --> 00:17:27.331
I think you're letting her off
a little easy. man.

510
00:17:27.331 --> 00:17:29.469
[Dispatch] All available trucks.
there is a Malinois

511
00:17:29.469 --> 00:17:32.609
pacing the outer guardrail
of the Cherry Creek Bridge.

512
00:17:32.643 --> 00:17:33.410
That's Hopper.

513
